persons:
    person-qyburn:
        properties:
            gender: male
            name:
                value: Qyburn
                fields:
                    given: Qyburn
        notes: "A former maester of the Citadel, stripped of his chain for 'opening the bodies of the living' to study the nature of death (the Citadel considers this a crime). Despite losing his chain, he retains his knowledge. Previously served with the Brave Companions (Vargo Hoat's company) at Harrenhal, where he treated Jaime Lannister's stump after his hand was cut off — saving Jaime's arm and life. Physically described as old but with more ash than snow in his grey hair, laugh lines around his mouth, and a shabby frayed robe (he has a torn sleeve badly sewn). He is found at the scene of Tywin's death and impresses Cersei with his competence and discretion. He is given custody of the dying Gregor Clegane to study the thickened manticore venom and conduct experiments — the Citadel cannot stop him in the black cells. He identifies the venom as manticore venom 'thickened possibly by sorcery.' Cersei appoints him to investigate Tyrion's escape; he finds Rugen's coin (a pre-Conquest Gardener coin of Garth the Twelfth) hidden under a chamber pot. He secures Cersei's secrets with his 'little birds' (Varys's network he inherits). He is unfailingly respectful, addressing her as 'Your Grace' and 'my queen.' His experiments on Gregor eventually produce 'Ser Robert Strong' (later chapters). (AFFC Cersei I, II; citation-affc-cersei-i, citation-affc-cersei-ii)"
